From: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
Date: Thu, 14 May 2026 00:55:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] wifi: ath12k: allow forcing dualmac fw via DT property

QCN9274 boards that physically wire out both MAC0 and MAC1 (e.g. used as
combined 5 GHz + 6 GHz radio on a single chip, like GL.iNet Flint 3) need
the dualmac AMSS firmware. ath12k selects between single-mac and dualmac
firmware based on a board-id flag read from chip OTP fuses, but on boards
where the OTP is not provisioned (board_id == 0xff), the driver falls back
to single-mac firmware. The chip then fails to bring up MAC1 ("HTC Service
WMI MAC1 connect request failed").

Allow boards to express the dualmac requirement via a DT property
`qcom,ath12k-prefer-dualmac` on the PCIe wifi child node. When the property
is present and OTP didn't already indicate dualmac, force dualmac firmware
selection.

Signed-off-by: Percival <perceivalpercy@gmail.com>
---
--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mhi.c
+++ b/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath12k/mhi.c
@@ -347,6 +347,15 @@ int ath12k_mhi_register(struct ath12k_pc
 		}
 	}
 
+	if (!dualmac &&
+	    device_property_read_bool(ab->dev, "qcom,ath12k-prefer-dualmac")) {
+		dualmac = true;
+		ath12k_dbg(ab, ATH12K_DBG_BOOT,
+			   "dualmac fw forced via DT (OTP board_id %#x lacks dualmac flag)\n",
+			   ath12k_pci_read32(ab, ab->hw_params->otp_board_id_register) &
+			   OTP_BOARD_ID_MASK);
+	}
+
 	if (dualmac) {
 		if (ab->fw.amss_dualmac_data && ab->fw.amss_dualmac_len > 0) {
 			/* use MHI firmware file from firmware-N.bin */
